3. cs.DS (Distributed Systems) - The paper deals with distributed systems security and proposes schemes to enable secure multi-party numerical computations in a Peer-to-Peer network. 
4. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the use of information theory in designing secure multi-party computation schemes for a Peer-to-Peer network.
